    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-04T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-04T19:00:00-05:00" n="143"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2732: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-04T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 4, 1933—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 5—12:23 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Department’s telegram No. 2, January 4, 11 a.m.<note n="3a" xml:id="d143fn3a"
                        >See footnote 2, above.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>(1)</label>
                    <item>Polo<note n="4" xml:id="d143fn4">Solón Polo. Chief Permanent Secretary,
                            Peruvian Foreign Office.</note> states this Government is only too
                        willing to support the action of the Neutrals but does not specifically
                        state what steps are proposed.</item>
                    <label>(2)</label>
                    <item>Immediately upon receiving request of December 31 Foreign Office cabled
                        Argentina, Brazil, and Chile inquiring their respective point of view and
                        suggesting action would be more effective if four neighboring nations act in
                        unison. Peru is awaiting replies which are expected shortly. Reporting
                        further soon.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
